.TH "generate-admin-account.bash" "1" "2022-10-10" "user manual" ""
.hy
.SH NAME
.PP
generate-admin-account.bash
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
generate-admin-account.bash USERNAME [GITHUB_USERNAME]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
generate-admin-account.bash sets up an admin user account per DLD group
practice for Ubuntu GNU/Linux machines.
In addition to adding the user it adds the groups we use to admin a
machine, creates a README.1st file in the home directory with
instructions to change the password and pulls ssh public keys from
GitHub for the user we\[cq]re creating.
.PP
The script should be run using sudo.
.SH EXAMPLE
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
sudo generate-admin-account.bash jane.doe
\f[R]
.fi
.PP
This would create an admin account for jane.doe.
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
sudo generate-admin-account.bash jane.doe jdeo
\f[R]
.fi
.PP
This could create an account for jane.doe with the GitHub username of
jdoe.
